│ logic for icmp instructions with the 'samesign' attribute.\n\n2. Analyzing  │
│ `opt`'s Log: The log shows that EarlyCSE incorrectly performs CSE between   │
│ `%icmp = icmp ugt i32 %zext, 31` and `%icmp.samesign = icmp samesign ugt    │
│ i32 %zext, 31`. These instructions are not equivalent because the           │
│ 'samesign' attribute changes the semantics - it indicates that both         │
│ operands are assumed to have the same sign, which can affect optimization   │
│ decisions.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis: The `SimpleValue::getHashValueImpl`   │
│ and `SimpleValue::isEqualImpl` functions in EarlyCSE.cpp only consider the  │
│ basic predicate (e.g., ICMP_UGT) when hashing and comparing icmp            │
│ instructions, but they ignore the 'samesign' attribute stored in the        │
│ instruction's SubclassOptionalData. This causes two semantically different  │
│ icmp instructions to be treated as identical, leading to incorrect CSE and  │
│ subsequent hash table corruption.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Points:\n   + Lines   │
│ 254-260 in llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/EarlyCSE.cpp: Modify the hashing      │
